My experience was when Rupert was in the garden with his men. I was at the kitchen door, leaning, sort of half listening to what was going on inside and half listening to what was outside. I didn't hear the house clear out, but the next voice I heard was, "Hello." I turned around, and... well, I don't know how I restrained myself from running and kissing her. It was as if my heart recognized her, but the brain didn't. I thought, "What are you doing? Control yourself."

I walked up, took her hand, and said, "I'm so glad you could come." And she just hugged me. It was such a wonderful experience. You can only relate it to your earthly mother if you've not seen her for years and suddenly you see her and think, "Ah, Mum!" You really want to go and run and hug and kiss them. Well, that's exactly how I felt. But, of course, your brain doesn't understand your heart, does it? Everything else that Rupert said is extremely accurate.

[The first speaker, Rupert, concludes]

Yeah, it was fantastic. Absolutely. For years I couldn't comprehend what was going on that night. For about two years, I didn't believe these vibrations were coming from me. I kept saying, "There's a door open somewhere." I couldn't comprehend this cool breeze. And even when I did, it didn't make a lot of sense to me because I was brought up in a different culture. People would say, "This is the Kundalini." And I thought, "Okay, well, so what?"